article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 73, William Woods 53
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Mitch Reuter scored 17 points and all but one player scored for Central Arkansas in a 73-53 rout of William Woods on Wednesday night. Brian Marks added nine points and a game-high 12 rebounds for the Bears (4-3), who shot 53 percent from the field in building a 44-32 lead by halftime. Reuter, a junior forward, added seven rebounds and three assists. Justin Cornelius had 12 points to lead William Woods (4-7). Jerone Lester added 10 points and nine rebounds, but the Owls were undone by 30.5 shooting from the field and hitting just four of 19 3-point attempts.
